Friday, September 27, 2019

Twenty - Twenty

     [TPP-2020-Calendar.jpg]
   It is hard to believe it will be 2020 in just a few months. I
   remember when my oldest daughters soccer team was named
   the Y2K bugs because that was the year all the computers were
   going to crash and the internet was going to fall apart. Well
   that did not happen, thankfully and here we are 20 years later ready
   to ring in 2020 with That Patchwork Place's beautiful Quilt Calendar.
   [3-March-Sheryl-Johnson.jpg]
   I am so excited to have one of my Quirky Little Quilts featured
   in the calendar. I always wanted to be a calendar girl!
   The photos are lovely and each month comes with
   complete instructions for the featured project.
   If you would like to order a copy for yourself you can do so here.
   Posted by Sheryl Johnson at 5:00 AM 1 comment:
   Email ThisBlogThis!Share to TwitterShare to FacebookShare to Pinterest

