Monday, September 16, 2019

Mini Monday Giveaway Winner

   [IMG-0714.JPG]
   So sorry for the delay in announcing this months mini winner.
   For the last 10 days I have been road tripping to and from
   Idaho. We helped our youngest daughter, her husband
   and yes, my new grandson Cooper with their move.
   The winner of this months mini is Laurel Lee Pedersen.
   She thinks this little quilt is Cute, Cute, Cute!!!
   Laurel send me an email with your shipping information
   and I will get your mini on its way to you.
   P.S. If you loved this month mini you can
   download the free pattern for it here.
   Posted by Sheryl Johnson at 5:00 AM 2 comments:
